 Basically someone said that AC above 1100 was not optimally effective.  Example: a piece of armor that would add 10 pts to your AC at AC 1030 would only add 3 pts if you put it on at 1110.<br>
<br>
I didn't think much about it.  At the time I was low level, and I never figured it would be an issue for me.<br>
<br>
Well, last night my AC crossed the 1100 barrier for the first time (with buffs).  So I tried to research this so-called &quot;soft cap&quot;.  No luck.  I found references to it on some warrior pages.  But everybody was in the same boat as me:  they remembered that somebody, sometime, had said something about some kind of soft cap.  No one had first hand experience.  No solid details.<br>
<br>
Does anybody here know anything about this?  Is there something special about 1100 AC?<br>
<br>
Belatucadros Spiritslammer<br>
Clan Spiritslammer<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udantesdedurre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dantes DeDurre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://forums.eqrealms.com/ubb/icons/icon10.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Splinterboy</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/9/01 3:49:13 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://valorblade.eqrealms.com/dantes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Soft Cap?</span><hr size=1> Well one thing that's good about most warrior armor is that we can get some great AC in addition to great stats.  1200 AC is a pretty high goal, but I wouldn't entirely destroy my DEX, resistances, and STR just for AC, especially if I was already hitting 1100.  I hear there really isn't much difference between 1000 and 1100 anyways.  So the difference between 1100 and 1200 may be even smaller. <p><TABLE width="299">
