Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 812<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/11/01 11:33:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead.jpg BORDER=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Soft Cap?</span><hr size=1> I just broke 800ish self buffed and I'm looking to get up over 900 so the bad guys won't beat me down as fast while they're trying to get at Awea hiding behind me.<br>
<br>
The thing with the 1000ac pre kunark was that they did a calculation of the theoretical maximum for a warrior in all the best ac gear and then called that 1000ac. They then took that actual ac number and scaled all ac values as a percentage of it to give the displayed ac. With kunark and now vellious that theoretical maximum kinda got kicked in the balls and tossed, but they still left the percentage calculation in place so that everyone wouldn't suddenly see their ac drop.<br>
<br>
Haven't heard anything about a soft cap, but I haven't worked with more than one or two people that were close enough to 1100AC for it to come into play. All I know is no matter where they start, I see a difference in the damage they're taking over time when I toss on the ac buff. <p><A HREF="mailto:Hethral@telus.net"><IMG SRC="http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/Signatures/HethralBanner.jpg" HEIGHT="150" BORDER="0"></A><BR>
